ython\r\na = LPIPS(net=\"alex\", verbose=False)\r\nx = torch.rand(4, 3, 256, 256)\r\ny = torch.rand(4, 3, 256, 256)\r\nz = a(x, y, normalize=True)\r\nprint(z)\r\n```\r\nWhile looking at the values contained in `res` (defined in the `forward()`), I have noticed that the implementation does not match the `Eq. 1` from the paper.\r\n\r\nHere's Eq. 1:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11836548/125159455-5e05f400-e16f-11eb-916d-214eec17cbbd.png)\r\n\r\nWhile this is what is implemented,\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11836548/125159495-a02f3580-e16f-11eb-82cd-61d6adad0f6f.png)\r\n\r\nThe square operation `** 2` at line 94 should be removed and instead applied on the `self.lins[kk].model(diffs[kk])` (at lines 98 and 100), and on `diff[kk]` (at lines 103 and 105).\r\n\r\nThanks in advance,\r\n\r\nGuillaume\r\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/richzhang/PerceptualSimilarity/issues/72/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/richzhang/PerceptualSimilarity/issues/72/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}